Robert Kushner lost his varsity coaching job at the Jack M . 
  Barrack Hebrew Academy after testifying this week about his years selling marijuana . 
  Kushner, 32, is one of more than a dozen former drug dealers testifying for the federal government about allegations of police wrongdoing . 
  He told jurors that some of the undercover officers on trial had stolen $81,000 in cash and 7 pounds of marijuana from him during a 2007 arrest . 
 